'''Puss in Boots''' sometimes also listed as ''Cannon Movie Tales: Puss in Boots'' (film, run time 1 hour 36 min) was a 1988 musical version of the story of [[Puss in Boots (fairy tale)|Puss in Boots]], starring [[Christopher Walken]] as "Puss" and [[Jason Connery]] as the youngest son who is assisted by Puss.  The film was directed by [[Eugene Marner]], the screenplay was by Carole Lucia Satrina.


